<br>
We are located at:  <a href=http://www.hunger-city.com target="_blank">www.hunger-city.com</a> and we offer realtime chatrooms where our game is played 24/7, and it's free.  The Hunger City RPG is also a published book.  Read on to find out what we're all about. <br>
<br>
A new RPG set in the time after the Third Civil War, the days following the end of recorded history.  Patrol the streets on horseback as a Knight trying to keep order in a world without morals.  Huddle in the skeleton of a burnt out skyscrapper with a Pride of Streeters, hoping only to see another night, praying only to find food to fill your belly. Run with a Pack of Terrorists collecting organs, or eyes, to sell to the Chop Shops.  Collect credits for the Temple as a Priest of Pep'si, ministering to the sick and dying, for a price, or wander the streets of Hunger City as a fearsome Kermit.  Enormous, green, with claws that can cut metal, and thick skin that even the best blade can rarely scathe, Kermits are the product of scientists tampering with genes to create the ultimate warrior. <br>
<br>
What do you think?  Hunger City is waiting for you.  On Love Me Avenue you might find a street corner Challenge, where you may pit your fighting skills against another's to earn twenty or thirty credits. Castle, the owner of the Hole in the Head, offers prime contracts, and occasionally she brings in the electric chair.  Stay in the chair the longest and earn a couple hundred credits, no one has been killed in the chair in nearly a half cycle. <br>
<br>
Gambling more your style?  For thirty-five credits you can get into Central Arena.  Watch Centurians and Gladiators fight here, a winning bet could earn you a fortune in credits.  Central Arena too credit rich for your blood?  On any street corner Promoters and their lovely assisstants will take your bet on impromptu Challenges.  Way down on Clinton Avenue Kermit races are common, and any event is one where betting is permitted, and encouraged. <br>
<br>
Or are you a fast Kermit, or Kermit Jockey,  the only rule in Kermit racing is the rider must finish on the back of his Kermit.  Knocking another rider from his Kermit with the blade of an axe is considered good form, and it is the rare Kermit race that does not invole a fatality.  Start racing on the streets, and move your way up through the small arena's until finally you're racing at Central Arena in front of a crowd of thousands. <br>
<br>
These are only a few possibilities. Hunger City waits for you.  Check us out at <a href=http://www.hunger-city.com target="_blank">www.hunger-city.com</a>. <br>
<br>
Thank you for your time, looking forward to seeing you online! <br>
